Methods of working with GitHub:

========================================================================

- cross-platform (esp. macOS) - Conda (mostly for scientific computing).
   = Anaconda channels do NOT have the packages to install GitHub CLI.
   = THIS MAY WORK :
     # Download Conda installer : 
     wget https://repo.anaconda.com/miniconda/Miniconda3-latest-Linux-x86_64.sh
     # Run the installer script : 
     bash Miniconda3-latest-Linux-x86_64.sh
     # Activate the (base) Conda environment : 
     source ~/miniconda3/bin/activate
     # Run Conda with ... :
     conda
     # Create a Conda env for GitHub CLI : 
     conda create --name gh
     # Activate the env : 
     conda activate gh
     # Use Conda to install GitHub CLI : 
     conda install gh --channel conda-forge

