Rejected (partly):

 - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

Method: via HTTPS, personal access tokens = passwords. 

Classic personal access tokens:
 + Access to important frameworks like REST and GraphQL API.
 + Extensible security (adding an expiry date).
 - Greater access + longer usability = less secure. 

Fine-grained personal access tokens:
 + More secure = ...
 - ... Limited permissions/access to other areas + ...
 - ... Shorter duration of access. 
 ? Specific permissions with more control over certain things. 

